submit your choreography to firework arts at stanford university presented by sica home search this site arts enews subscribe for students opportunities submit your choreography to firework deadline friday march 30 2012 unpaid the dance division announces spring quarter performance opportunity for student choreographers and dancers firework dances on by for stanford dancers performance dates fri sat april 27 28 at 8 pm in roble studio 38 firework is a dance division sponsored student works concert of dances on by and for stanford dancers this year the firework concert will run for two nights and it will be as fully theatrical as participating students make it to be considered for the concert follow these simple steps 1 submit an email request to be on the program 2 ask a dance division faculty member to mentor your dance you must have a mentor to be on the program there is a modest budget for lighting costumes scenic elements press and program materials post performance reception participating choreographers will agree upon plan and implement all aspects of the concert together there will be basic technical supervision for student led crews and production support all kinds of dance welcome all dancers encouraged to apply dance will be broadly defined questions email diane frank dfrank1 stanford edu contact dfrank1 stanford edu for more info listed in auditions submissions see all opportunities prospective students check out the arts guide your multimedia guide to the arts at stanford stay updated student home events calendar opportunities in review subscribe curricular info majoring minoring creativity course guide arts intensive arts immersion arts circle make it happen money supplies space collaboration promotion beyond stanford internships career resources bay area arts back to arts at stanford make a gift volunteer login press sitemap contact connect twitter facebook vimeo flickr 2011 stanford university all rights reserved local user login
